727445f.title: Queens: Myrtle Avenue - Woodhaven Boulevard
727445f.text:
Myrtle Ave., west of Woodhaven Boulevard, showing in the foreground
. bridge over a division right of way of the Long Island Railroad.
September 8, 1933.
Trvin Fitterman.

727446f.title: Queens: Myrtle Avenue - Woodhaven Boulevard
727446f.text:
Myrtle Avenue, east from Woodhaven Boulevard, showing the
thoroughfare entering Forest Park after crossing the small
bridge over the Long Island Railroad tracks.
Trvin Fitterman
727446f.folder: Myrtle Avenue & Woodhaven Boulevard, Queens, NY

727447f-a.title: Queens: Myrtle Avenue - Woodhaven Boulevard
727447f-a.text:
Myrtle Ave. (tracks thereon), at the S.W. corner of Woodhaven
Boulevard (formerly Trotting Course Lane), showing the former Eldorado
Roadhouse built by one Koenig in what was Koenig Park. One Nammerer
was the owner in 1891. This place was still standing in 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
